---
description: Protect sync compatibility and data model invariants
globs:
  - "src/types.ts"
  - "src/db.ts"
  - "src/firebase/**/*.ts"
  - "src/utils/syncCompare.ts"
  - "src/utils/recurrence.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Sync Integrity Rule

- Preserve backward compatibility when extending the `Node` model.
- Any new persisted field must be propagated through:
  - local DB paths (`src/db.ts`)
  - Firebase normalization/sync (`src/firebase/sync.ts`)
  - conflict comparison (`src/utils/syncCompare.ts`)
- Do not silently change conflict semantics; document intentional behavior updates.
- Avoid breaking shape assumptions used by sync workers and notifications.
- If a change touches recurring/deadline semantics, validate schedule generation paths.
